revision.text:
[[File:Gender_Example.png|thumb|A wild female Pelipper in the Insular Sea Route.]]

=Description=
Gender are a visual difference that some Pokémon get acess to, Pokémon that don't have acess to that mechanic are usually called "Genderless". A few Pokémon have a design changed depending on their Gender, such as Venusaur getting a seed on its flower if it's female. some Pokémons can also always be a Gender, like Chansey being always female.

=Gender Variations=

==Gender Exclusive==
These Pokémon Genders are always Male or Female.

